PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778652345
OL,3,CAlmost two thirds of Britons would
OL,4,Cback smoke-free pub gardens ` poll
OL,6,FHazel Cheeseman, chief executive of
OL,7,FAsh, said: "Smoke-free laws have been
OL,8,Fone of the biggest public health
OL,9,Fsuccess stories in recent decades, but
OL,10,Fmillions of people are still exposed
OL,11,Fto harmful second-hand smoke in
OL,12,Foutdoor settings.
OL,14,F"The public is clear that they want
OL,15,Fmore places where they can breathe
OL,16,Fclean air. As ministers review the
OL,17,Ffindings from the consultation, there
OL,18,Fis a strong mandate to go further and
OL,19,Ffaster.
OL,26,@oD@LOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778652345
OL,3,CAlmost two thirds of Britons would
OL,4,Cback smoke-free pub gardens ` poll
OL,6,F"Extending smoke-free laws to areas
OL,7,Flike pub gardens, all play areas,
OL,8,Funiversity campuses and transport hubs
OL,9,Fis a common-sense next step that will
OL,10,Fprotect health and support a smoke-
OL,11,Ffree generation."
OL,13,FGovernment estimates suggest the
OL,14,FTobacco and Vapes Bill could slash the
OL,15,Ftotal number of smokers aged 14 and
OL,16,Fover to 701,167 in 2056 from 5,502,164
OL,17,Fin 2023.
OL,19,FThe modelling also estimates that some
OL,20,F154,800 deaths will be prevented in
OL,21,FEngland by 2100.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
